<paragraph id="36137272B30AF82576F2FAA15F171C4C" blockId="11.[151,1437,1361,2027]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF82576F2FAA15D4A1F2C" bold="true" box="[151,285,1361,1387]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
This species was examined in detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="523D0F83B30AF825749CFAA15FC31F2C" author="Inoue" box="[761,916,1361,1387]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refString="Inoue, H. (1971) The Geometridae of the Ryukyu Islands (Lepidoptera). Bulletin of Faculty of Domestic Sciences, Otsuma Woman's University, 7, 141 - 179." type="journal article" year="1971">
Inoue (
<number id="80646055B30AF8257528FAA15FDB1F2C" box="[845,908,1361,1387]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who first described and illustrated the male and female genitalia. Based mostly on facies and wing venation, 
<bibRefCitation id="523D0F83B30AF82575EAFA8958701FD4" author="Inoue" box="[911,1063,1401,1427]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refString="Inoue, H. (1971) The Geometridae of the Ryukyu Islands (Lepidoptera). Bulletin of Faculty of Domestic Sciences, Otsuma Woman's University, 7, 141 - 179." type="journal article" year="1971">
Inoue (
<number id="80646055B30AF8257584FA8958491FD4" box="[993,1054,1401,1427]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
tentatively assigned the species to 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF82576D3FA515D2A1FFD" box="[182,381,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF82576D3FA515D2A1FFD" box="[182,381,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Nipponogelasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the male of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF82574F1FA515FE81FFD" box="[660,959,1441,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mixochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF82574F1FA515FE81FFD" box="[660,959,1441,1466]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Mixochlora chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a large conical distal process on the sacculus, which occurs very rarely in 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF8257430FA395EA71FA4" box="[597,752,1481,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
. In the Palaearctic region and in South 
<collectingCountry id="4EBB32E2B30AF82572A4FA3959661FA4" box="[1217,1329,1481,1507]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">East Asia</collectingCountry>
this process is known only in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF8257474FA015F6B1C4C" authority="Warren, 1893" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" box="[529,828,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF8257474FA015EC51C4D" box="[529,658,1521,1546]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Microloxia</emphasis>
Warren, 
<number id="80646055B30AF825749BFA015F6B1C4C" box="[766,828,1521,1547]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" value="1893.0">1893</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7EB621F9B30AF82276A2F9E95D881B38" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph id="36137272B30AF82576A2F9E95EE81DAC" blockId="11.[151,1437,1361,2027]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF82577ABF9E95EAD1C75" box="[462,762,1561,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mixochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF82577ABF9E95EAD1C75" box="[462,762,1561,1586]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Mixochlora chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share with those of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF825758BF9E959CB1C74" authority="Hubner, 1813" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1813" box="[1006,1436,1561,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herbaria">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF825758BF9E958881C75" box="[1006,1247,1561,1586]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Microloxia herbaria</emphasis>
(Hübner, 
<number id="80646055B30AF825733DF9E959C31C74" box="[1368,1428,1561,1587]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" value="1813.0">1813</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(the 
<typeStatus id="E917CCD0B30AF82576A9F9B15CA91C1C" box="[204,254,1601,1627]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus) the following characters: uncus with short bifurcation at the apex; socii similar to uncus in length and shape; valva simple, elongate, with long, broad, slightly convex costa; sacculus with long, conical distal process reaching 
<number id="80646055B30AF8257428F9615E0B1CEC" box="[589,604,1681,1707]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number id="80646055B30AF8257400F9615E251CEC" box="[613,626,1681,1707]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" value="5.0">5</number>
length of valva; transtilla broad, platelike; saccus long, conical; and aedeagus simple, lacking cornuti (morphological data on 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF8257551F9495FE21C95" box="[820,949,1721,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF8257551F9495FE21C95" box="[820,949,1721,1746]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Microloxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the description and figures in 
<bibRefCitation id="523D0F83B30AF8257333F9495D701CBC" author="Hausmann" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refString="Hausmann, A. (1995) Revision der altweltlichen Arten der Gattung Microloxia Warren, 1893 (Lepidoptera, Geometridae: Geometrinae). Atalanta, 25 (3 / 4), 571 - 608." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hausmann, 
<number id="80646055B30AF825768FF9115D701CBC" box="[234,295,1761,1787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" value="1995.2001">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="523D0F83B30AF8257753F9115D221CBC" author="Hausmann" box="[310,373,1761,1787]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refString="Hausmann, A. (2001) Introduction. Archiearinae, Orthostixinae, Desmobathrinae, Alsophilinae, Geometrinae. In Hausmann, A. (ed.). The Geometrid Moths of Europe, vol. 1. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 282 pp." type="book" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
). In general, the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF825757FF911581F1CBD" box="[794,1096,1761,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mixochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF825757FF911581F1CBD" box="[794,1096,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Mixochlora chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF82576F2F8F95DD11D65" box="[151,390,1801,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herbaria">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF82576F2F8F95DD11D65" box="[151,390,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Microloxia herbaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; they differ from the latter by the narrower socii, broader saccus, longer basal process of the aedeagus, and longer ventral processes of the transtilla. However, males of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF8257252F8C159351D0D" box="[1079,1378,1841,1866]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mixochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF8257252F8C159351D0D" box="[1079,1378,1841,1866]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Mixochlora chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possess a long needlelike posterior process on the eighth abdominal sternite that is absent in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF82576F2F8715D4F1DDD" box="[151,280,1921,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF82576F2F8715D4F1DDD" box="[151,280,1921,1946]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Microloxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the female genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF825745BF8715F3E1DDD" box="[574,873,1921,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mixochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF825745BF8715F3E1DDD" box="[574,873,1921,1946]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Mixochlora chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30AF8257261F87158A31DDD" box="[1028,1268,1921,1946]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herbaria">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30AF8257261F87158A31DDD" box="[1028,1268,1921,1946]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="66">Microloxia herbaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the possession of a short ductus bursae and a rounded sacklike corpus bursae, but both species share a very characteristic signum consisting of two small, toothed plates.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="36137272B30DF82276A2FF685D881B38" blockId="12.[151,1436,152,423]" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">
External characters provide support for the transfer of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF822752FFF6858211AF6" box="[842,1142,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mixochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30DF822752FFF6858211AF6" box="[842,1142,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">Mixochlora chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF82272F8FF6859491AF6" box="[1181,1310,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30DF82272F8FF6859491AF6" box="[1181,1310,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">Microloxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including Inoue's note on similarity of wing venation of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF82274D9FF3058671A9D" authority="Prout" authorityName="Prout" box="[700,1072,192,218]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Mixochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30DF82274D9FF305FBF1A9E" box="[700,1000,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">Mixochlora chlorissoides</emphasis>
Prout
</taxonomicName>
with that of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF82272B0FF305CAD1B46" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immunis">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30DF82272B0FF305CAD1B46" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">Nipponogelasma immunis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (= 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF8227755FF185DA21B46" box="[304,501,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Aoshakuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucia">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30DF8227755FF185DA21B46" box="[304,501,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">Aoshakuna lucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In the last species the forewing has a very short free basal portion of R 
<number id="80646055B30DF8227329FF0859031B41" box="[1356,1364,248,262]" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
fused with Sc for a long distance, a condition that rarely occurs in 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF8227538FEE25FAF1B6B" box="[861,1016,274,300]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Geometrinae">Geometrinae</taxonomicName>
; the same configuration of Sc–R 
<number id="80646055B30DF822731CFED359D61B76" box="[1401,1409,291,305]" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" value="1.0">1</number>
is shown on the figure of the wing venaton of 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF82274D5FECE5FF41B10" box="[688,931,318,343]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herbaria">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30DF82274D5FECE5FF41B10" box="[688,931,318,343]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">Microloxia herbaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F1AC09F1B30DF8227585FECE59231B10" authority="Rebel, 1894" authorityName="Rebel" authorityYear="1894" box="[992,1396,317,343]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simonyi">
<emphasis id="04D8AE60B30DF8227585FECE58901B10" box="[992,1223,318,343]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="67">Microloxia simonyi</emphasis>
(Rebel, 
<number id="80646055B30DF8227355FECD593B1B10" box="[1328,1388,317,343]" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" value="1894.0">1894</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="523D0F83B30DF82276F2FE955D8C1B38" author="Hausmann" box="[151,475,357,383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" refString="Hausmann, A. (1995) Revision der altweltlichen Arten der Gattung Microloxia Warren, 1893 (Lepidoptera, Geometridae: Geometrinae). Atalanta, 25 (3 / 4), 571 - 608." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hausmann (
<number id="80646055B30DF8227741FE955D331B38" box="[292,356,357,383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" value="1995.0">1995</number>
: figs 
<number id="80646055B30DF82277C7FE955D851B38" box="[418,466,357,383]" pageId="12" pageNumber="67" value="1.2">1, 2</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
